  "texts": [
    "The curriculum could start with an introductory course on basics of AI and generative AI models, covering essential concepts like machine learning, neural networks, and generative AI techniques such as GANs, VAEs and transformers, which could include hands-on exercises to familiarize students with applications of generative AI tools such as ChatGPT or medical-specific models.",
    "Introduction to Generative AI tools can be done in early stages of training to support self-directed learning and strengthen core orthopedic concepts through interactive modules and virtual case studies.",
    "These tools can supplement traditional didactic learning by offering opportunities for self-directed practice and personalized feedback.",
    "As students advance, generative AI applications can be incorporated into clinical simulations, enabling them to interact with realistic patient scenarios that reinforce clinical reasoning and decision-making skills.",
    "Subsequent coursework might address role of AI-powered VR simulations in surgical planning and training."
  ],
